---
title: Chicken & Apple Rosemary Pan Sauce with Mashed Potatoes & Roasted Brussels Sprouts
description: Friends, these are not your average pork chops. In fact, our chefs gave ’em a restaurant-worthy makeover, transforming them to something above and beyond. The chops are seared to perfection, and drizzled with an ultra-savory, rosemary-flecked apple pan sauce. The sides are just as impressive. We’re serving up creamy mashed potatoes and roasted Brussels sprouts to round everything out. Get ready for maximum dinnertime deliciousness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/63fe2b299bc0d9da070dbdba-bea9c14c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/654bde2033e04495c0a403c5.pdf
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 580 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 410 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-apple-rosemary-pan-sauce-654bde2033e04495c0a403c5
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve and core @apple{1} and dice one half into ¼-inch pieces (dice whole apple for 4 servings). Strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add diced apple and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring occasionally, until apple is slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{½%cup} (¾ cup for 4 servings), and @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4) into pan with apple mixture. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium. Cook until apple is tender and liquid has reduced, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in half the @Dijon mustard{1%tsp} (all for 4) and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted and combined. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer to a #medium microwave-safe bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wash out pan.

== Roasted Brussels Sprouts ==

Meanwhile, trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%oz} lengthwise. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

While Brussels sprouts roast, dice @potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Mash with @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), salt, and pepper until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chicken Cutlets ==

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for sauce over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Swap in chicken for pork; cook until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side.

== Serving ==

Divide Brussels sprouts, mashed potatoes, and chicken between plates.

Top chicken with apple pan sauce and serve.

> TIP: If sauce has cooled, reheat in microwave for 30 seconds or return to pan with a splash of water; cook over medium heat, stirring, until warm.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.